Remember speed dial? Speed dating? Speed skating? Well get ready for speed dinner–from box to plate in 15 minutes (or less!), and it's no slouch. Lean, old-school, beefy steak is quick seared, then finished with garlic-herb butter and drizzled with a mustard cream sauce. It's served with a side of buttery steamed potatoes, and a fresh mixed green salad. A real homey, robust, and fuss-free meal idea for any weeknight.

== Potatoes and Butter ==

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @potatoes{12%ounce}. Cut @tomato{1}(quartered) into wedges.

Place potatoes and half the @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} in a #microwave-safe bowl{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until tender, ~{6-7%minutes}. Keep covered.

== Steak ==

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry and season with salt and pepper. Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot pan. Cook steak to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

To finish steak, add remaining garlic herb butter and spoon over. Transfer to a #cutting board{}; reserve butter in pan.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Creamy Mustard Sauce ==

In a second microwave-safe bowl, mix half the @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, half the @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of pepper. Cover with plastic wrap; microwave ~{40%seconds}.

== Salad ==

In a third #bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce}, tomato, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, half the @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}; season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Spoon melted butter over steak. Serve with salad and potatoes. Drizzle with creamy mustard sauce.